-1683258342.text: "FD cells had 50-80% less intracellular folate, associated with aberrant hypomethylation of the Shh promoter, than control cells, and increased binding of nuclear NF-kappaB subunit p65 to the Shh promoter region, which coincided with increased Shh expression and protein production of Shh ligand; in addition, the FD induced Shh signaling targeted Gli1 transcription activator as well as Ptch receptor."
